A state-of-the-art swimming pool which has been built for babies and toddlers is to open in West Sussex.The aquatic facility in Washington, near Steyning, has been transformed from a disused warehouse.Splash Cove will feature a 10x5m pool with technology and facilities for children learning to swim and swimming teachers.Opening on July 8, it will offer a new space for 300 babies and children under 10.
The project is to be managed by Bell Leisure Pools and Water Babies.Caroline Braund, of Water Babies, said the pool will allow children to “learn a skill for life”.“We’re thrilled with the final product, which gives customers a premium swimming experience,” she said.Lawrence Pearce, director at Bell Leisure, added: “We wanted to utilise this unused space to create a brand-new location for families to enjoy and learn to swim.”
